In this podcast, we will witness NEET success stories of two sisters, Haadia Umam from ASMC Firozabad and Shanib Fatima from KSGMC Bulandshahr, who both Cracked the NEET exam on their second attempts.

Haadia, initially a physiotherapy student, reignited her dream of pursuing MBBS and decided to prepare for NEET once again. She discussed this with her father and canceled her admission form physiotherapy and prepared for NEET 2022, With just four months left , she embarked on a rigorous preparation schedule. In her next attempt of 2023 she cracked NEET and got a government medical college.

Shanib‚Äôs journey began in 2023 when she decided to crack NEET in her first attempt but eventually succeeded in NEET 2024. Finding a conducive environment in a library and a companion to study with, Shanib adopted a similar last month strategy for NEET, emphasizing mock tests and extensive practice.

Both sisters were part of the Target Batch of NEETprep and have shared crucial insights on how to crack NEET, particularly focusing on what to do in the last month before the exam. In this podcast, they double down on the importance of a robust last month strategy for NEET 2025, advising aspirants to enhance their preparation by practicing through NEET mock tests and solving as many questions as possible.

Interestingly, many people misguided them to focus on boards in class 12th and after that take a drop for NEET, but now both of them suggest that NEET can be cracked along with class 12th board exams

Whether you are preparing for NEET 2025 or seeking effective strategies on how to crack NEET, this podcast is packed with motivational stories and practical tips that can significantly elevate your preparation. Subscribe to our channel for more NEET strategies and insights directly from top performers like Haadia and Shanib.
